<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mongolian President, Delegation Continue Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Nouhak, Ochirbat Sign Treaty </H4>
<F P=102> BK0403104894 Vientiane KPL in English 0901 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0403104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, March 4 (KPL) -- Lao PDR [People's 
Democratic Republic] President Nouhak Phoumsavan and Mongolian 
President Punsalmaagiyn Ochirbat yesterday signed here a 
friendship treaty between Laos and Mongolia. 
  The treaty provides that the parties will develop their 
relations on the basis of principles generally recognised by the 
international law: respect for each other's independence and 
sovereignty, non-interference in each other's internal affairs, 
equality and mutual benefit, respect for the fundamental human 
rights and freedom and peaceful solutions to conflicts. 
  The parties will promote their cooperation in political and 
economic fields including trade, technical science, public 
health, culture, education, press, humanitarian affairs and 
others to their mutual interest. [Words indistinct] also 
provided in the treaty to replace the friendship and cooperation 
treaty signed in 1979 between the two countries when this treaty 
has become effective, which means after it has been ratified and 
after the date an exchange of letter for the ratification of 
this treaty has been made. 
  On the same day, an agreement concerning investment 
promotion 
and protection between the two countries was also signed between 
Minister Phao Bounnaphon, head of the Prime Minister's Office, 
and the trade and industry minister of Mongolia. The agreement 
has the objectives to promote and create conditions favorable 
for investment by each party in one another's country in 
conformity with the law of their countries. Each party will 
provide facilities, fair treatment, and protection as well as 
giving priorities to each other in investment sectors and in 
remitting profit, dividend to their respective countries. 
  The signing of this agreement was witnessed by the 
presidents 
of the two countries, and senior officials from both sides. 
  The friendship treaty and the investment promotion and 
protection agreement between Laos and Mongolia were signed 
during a three-day visit to Laos by Mongolian President 
Punsalmaagiyn Ochirbat and his delegation. The Mongolian 
president with his wife and delegation left here yesterday for 
Hanoi for a visit to Vietnam. 
  While in Laos, the Mongolian president had talks with 
President Nouhak Phoumsavan and met with Prime Minister Khamtai 
Siphandon, who invited [words indistinct]. He also (?paid a 
visit) [words indistinct] Mekong bridge construction project, 
and the Nam Ngum hydropower dam in the province of Vientiane. 
  An official ceremony to see the Mongolian president and his 
delegation off was held at the Presidential Palace. 

</TEXT>

